Brown steak. Drain, discarding all but 2 tablespoons drippings. Set meat aside. Saute onion and garlic in drippings for 3 minutes. Return meat to pan. Add tomato sauce, 1 cup water, V-8 juice, hot pepper sauce and spices; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 2-1/2 hours. Combine flour with remaining water; whisk into chili. Cook 10 minutes.